WEBVTT

00:15:29.440 --> 00:15:31.536
GS: I hope so. Otherwise, don't do it.

00:15:31.560 --> 00:15:35.296
AG: The easiest way to do that?
Make them shorter, much shorter.

00:15:35.320 --> 00:15:37.656
GS: I make sure
they're in 15-minute increments.

00:15:37.680 --> 00:15:40.296
Most people want them
to be in hour increments,

00:15:40.320 --> 00:15:42.456
but they don't need
to be in hour increments,

00:15:42.480 --> 00:15:47.056
so you can get through an awful lot more
if you schedule a little tighter.

00:15:47.080 --> 00:15:49.536
AG: How do I get this guy
to run my meetings?

00:15:49.560 --> 00:15:52.776
GS: Well, I'm trying to save
all the people who are now experiencing

00:15:52.800 --> 00:15:54.376
what I used to experience.

00:15:54.400 --> 00:15:56.080
You don't have to suffer like that.

00:15:57.000 --> 00:15:58.296
AG: Rule number one?

00:15:58.320 --> 00:16:00.256
Before you even schedule that meeting,